edu.umass.cs.gnsserver.gnsapp.clientCommandProcessor.commandSupport

Class AccountAccess

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.umass.cs.gnsserver.gnsapp.clientCommandProcessor.commandSupport.AccountAccess

  • public class AccountAccess
extends Object
    Provides the basic interface to GNS accounts.

    See AccountInfo for more details about accounts.

    Some of the internal records used to maintain account information are as follows:

    GUID: "ACCOUNT_INFO" -- {account} for primary guid
    GUID: "GUID" -- GUID (primary) for secondary guid
    GUID: "GUID_INFO" -- {guid info}
    HRN: "GUID" -- GUID

    GUID = Globally Unique Identifier
    HRN = Human Readable Name

    Author:
    westy, arun

      • addAccount

        public static CommandResponse addAccount(String name,
                                         String guid,
                                         String publicKey,
                                         String password,
                                         boolean emailVerify,
                                         String verifyCode,
                                         ClientRequestHandlerInterface handler)
        Create a new GNS user account. THIS CAN BYPASS THE EMAIL VERIFICATION if you set emailVerify to false;

        This adds three records to the GNS for the account:
        NAME: "_GNS_GUID" -- guid
        GUID: "_GNS_ACCOUNT_INFO" -- {account record - an AccountInfo object stored as JSON}
        GUID: "_GNS_GUID_INFO" -- {guid record - a GuidInfo object stored as JSON}

        Parameters:
        name -
        guid -
        publicKey -
        password -
        emailVerify -
        verifyCode -
        handler -
        Returns:
        status result

      • addGuid

        public static CommandResponse addGuid(AccountInfo accountInfo,
                                      GuidInfo accountGuidInfo,
                                      String name,
                                      String guid,
                                      String publicKey,
                                      ClientRequestHandlerInterface handler)
        Adds a new GUID associated with an existing account.

        These records will be created:
        GUID: "_GNS_PRIMARY_GUID" -- GUID (primary) for secondary guid
        GUID: "_GNS_GUID_INFO" -- {guid info}
        HRN: "_GNS_GUID" -- GUID

        Parameters:
        accountInfo - - the accountInfo of the account to add the GUID to
        accountGuidInfo -
        name - = the human readable name to associate with the GUID
        guid - - the new GUID
        publicKey - - the public key to use with the new account
        handler -
        Returns:
        status result
